        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-900/30 border-[2px] border-red-500/50 p-5 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-black text-lg text-white">Vague Value Proposition (74% make this)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">"Revolutionizing X with AI" tells me nothing. "AI that writes blog posts in your voice in 30 seconds" = specific value. 74% of startup sites have generic headline copy. Visitors bounce in 8 seconds. Clear value prop = understand instantly = sign up. Vague = "what does this do?" = bounce.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-900/30 border-[2px] border-red-500/50 p-5 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-black text-lg text-white">Founder Story Hidden (67% make this)</h3>
