        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-900/30 border-[2px] border-red-500/50 p-5 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-black text-lg text-white">Friction-heavy Signup (61% make this)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">Waitlist form asks: name, email, company, role, use case, how did you hear, referral code. 7 fields. 61% abandonment rate. Reduce to email-only. 53% higher conversion. Capture interest first, qualify later. Friction = abandonment. Simple = signups.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-900/30 border-[2px] border-red-500/50 p-5 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-black text-lg text-white">No Social Proof (54% make this)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">"Join our waitlist" only. Zero proof anyone cares. Add "500+ founders waiting" or "Backed by Y Combinator" or "Featured in TechCrunch." Social proof = momentum = join. No proof = "is this legit?" = skip. 54% of pre-launch sites have zero social proof. FOMO drives signups. Show it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-900/30 border-[2px] border-red-500/50 p-5 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-black text-lg text-white">Mobile Waitlist Broken (47% make this)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">Product Hunt = mobile browsing. Waitlist button tiny. Signup form microscopic. 47% of startup sites fail mobile testing. Mobile = 73% of Product Hunt traffic. Broken mobile = can't sign up = lost customer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

